TASK_TITLE=Fix doey-ctl status observe: factor staleness into active detection
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=bug
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W2
TASK_DESCRIPTION=CATEGORY: quick
MODEL: sonnet

BUG: doey-ctl status observe reports active: true for panes that are clearly idle, because it trusts the spinner glyph without checking staleness.

EVIDENCE: Worker at prompt (❯) for 7+ minutes. last_output_age_sec: 445, heartbeat_age_sec: null. But observe returned active: true because a 'Baked' glyph was still visible in the capture.

FIX: Add staleness thresholds to the active determination logic in observe_cmd.go:
- If last_output_age_sec > 60 AND (heartbeat_age_sec is null OR > 60) → active: false regardless of glyph
- Add a 'stale' field to the JSON output when glyph is present but staleness thresholds are exceeded
- The ❯ prompt check should take priority over glyph detection when both are present

KEY FILE: tui/cmd/doey-ctl/observe_cmd.go

This directly impacts the STATUS CHECK PROTOCOL used by Boss and all monitoring. False positives make status reports unreliable.
